    given-names: Amelia
    affiliation: "Universidad Nacional Intercultural de la Amazonía (UNIA)"
repository-code: "https://github.com/rzariquiey/kakataibo-intergenerational-variation"
abstract: >-
  Data and analysis scripts accompanying the study of intergenerational
  variation in switch-reference and clause-linkage strategies among
  Kakataibo (Pano, Peru) speakers. The corpus comprises Isakuna story
  narratives from 27 speakers divided into three generational cohorts
  (elderly, adult, young). Non-parametric statistical analyses
  (Kruskal-Wallis, Mann-Whitney U, Spearman ρ) document a systematic
  reduction in switch-reference density and structural complexity
  across generations.
keywords:
